sentences.english: A heart, which can bear beautiful expectation, will never wither.
sentences.chinese: 能生出美好指望的心是永远不会凋败的。

sentences.english: The fibre comes out in strands and is then spun into yarn on a spinning machine.
sentences.chinese: 纤维成缕生出，并纺在纺纱机的细纱上。

sentences.english: Accidentally, my Dachshund and Basset Hound gave birth to a mongrel.
sentences.chinese: 一不留神，我家的腊肠和巴吉度生出了一个混血种。
繁重的劳动使他的双手生出茧子来。

sentences.english: But these doctors are quietly confident that Derya will give birth to a healthy baby.
sentences.chinese: 但这些医生们对德亚能生出一个健康宝宝颇有信心。

sentences.english: They have unique knowledge, then give birth to a wise and class.
sentences.chinese: 他们既独有知识，于是生出了智愚的阶级。

sentences.english: Destined to give birth to little to harsh.
sentences.chinese: 有缘无情的要生出情来。

sentences.english: In the objective environment, wood friction makes fire.
sentences.chinese: 在客观环境中，木与木相互摩擦就会生出火苗。

sentences.english: Wurzel-chakra also create a white crystal ball, too.
sentences.chinese: 海底轮也生出了一颗白色的水晶球。

sentences.english: HEROD: [To Herodias] You see how you have brought up this daughter of yours.
sentences.chinese: 你看看，你怎么会生出这样的女儿。

sentences.english: Our derived document definition will add one more statement for each document.
sentences.chinese: 派生出的文档定义将为每个文档再添加一条语句。

sentences.english: Later men and women were born from the egg. They were ancestors of the Paiwan people.
sentences.chinese: 不久从蛋中破壳生出人类，即是排湾人的祖先。

sentences.english: Beauty may have fair leaves, yet bitter fruit.
sentences.chinese: 美丽长出漂亮白勺叶子，却生出苦辣白勺果实。

sentences.english: And God said, " Let the earth bring forth living creatures of every kind."
sentences.chinese: 神说，地要生出活物来，各从其类。

sentences.english: Light can cause potatoes to develop a poison called solanine .
sentences.chinese: 因为光线会导致马铃薯生出一种叫做茄碱的毒物。
